info.notes: Four-digit year in which the event occurred.
info.label: Year

info.notes: Two-digit month in which the event occurred. Records without valid months are excluded. The sum of counts by month for a given year may not equal the annual count.
info.label: Month

info.notes: Whether the geography is based on the place of residence or place of occurrence. A geography type of Residence includes events for California residents even if they occurred outside of California, whereas a geography type of Occurrence includes events that occurred within California even if they were not California residents.
info.label: Geography Type

info.notes: General demographic or detail category under which events have been stratified. For example, Race-Ethnicity or Gender. Will be Total Population if there is no stratification.
info.label: Strata

info.notes: Individual strata within the general demographic or detail category. For example, Hispanic or Female. Will be Total Population if there is no stratification.
info.label: Strata Name

info.notes: Count of events. If blank, see annotation for more information.
info.label: Count

info.notes: Annotation code for count as single digit: blank = no annotation; 1 = cell suppressed for small numbers; 2 = cell suppressed for complementary cell; 3 = no data is available; 4 = statistically unstable value.
info.label: Annotation Code

info.notes: Descriptive text for the data annotation.
info.label: Annotation Description

info.notes: For provisional data, date when the data was extracted (MM/DD/YYYY). Provisional counts are based on the data available when the data was extracted and may not represent all events that occurred during the time period.
info.label: Data Extraction Date

info.notes: Date data was created or revised (MM/DD/YYYY).
info.label: Data Revision Date
